xidants LLC personnel have been trained how to activate countermeasures and notify emergency response agencies. They have been trained how to assess the situation and communicate to emergency response personnel the most prudent course of action to take to safeguard the community. Merisol Antioxidants LLC management personnel will report to work on site with emergency responders as a resource for controlling releases of isobutylene, and for operating counter measure systems.  Merisol Antioxidants LLC personnel will assist the Incident Commander on the scene as specialists in handling isobutylene. The emergency plan is reviewed and resubmitted to the Venango County LEPC when updated for its review and approval. Necessary elements of the plan are incorporated into the Venango County Emergency Response Plan.  Periodic tabletop or deployment drills are conducted to keep emergency response personnel familiar with plant materials, emergency systems, and response measures.

Recent Changes to Improve Safety

Merisol Antioxidants LLC performs periodic process hazard analyses (safety reviews) of all chemical processes, including the isobutylene system. Some of the recently completed changes to improve the safety of the isobutylene storage and transfer system are listed below.


1) New higher pressure rated piping and gaskets were installed in isobutylene liquid and vapor service piping associated with the storage vessels and unloading in 2007 and 2008;
2) The addition of an automatic shutoff valve interlocked to LEL detection and fire systems for the vapor line connecting the unloading area to the storage vessels was completed in 2007;
3) Thermal expansion relief valves with discharge to the isobutylene storage vapor piping were added to the isobutylene charge and unloading liquid piping in 2007 to prevent over-pressure and releases;
4) Some older sections of isobutylene recovery piping were replaced in 2008 and all gaskets were upgraded in the recovery piping;
5) A Reactor LE

L perimeter monitoring system interlocked to shutdowns and foam/water deluge systems was installed in 2008;
6) A new isobutylene unloading compressor with enhanced safety features was installed in 2005;
7) Additional process LEL monitoring sensors interlocked to unit shutdowns and water deluge systems was added to the modified dealkylation unit in 2007; and
8) The excess flow valves on the isobutylene storage tanks were inspected and rebuilt in 2008.

Merisol Antioxidants LLC has a continuous improvement philosophy in all safety and environment issues.
